# Accessibility Development Rules

## Core Principles
- **Follow WCAG 2.1 AA standards** for all components and pages
- **Implement semantic HTML structure** with proper heading hierarchy
- **Ensure keyboard navigation support** for all interactive elements
- **Provide proper ARIA labels and descriptions** for complex components
- **Test with screen readers and assistive technologies** regularly
- **Support reduced motion preferences** and accessibility features

## Compliance and Standards

### WCAG 2.1 AA Requirements
- **Perceivable**: Content is available to all users
- **Operable**: Interface is navigable by all users
- **Understandable**: Content and operation are clear
- **Robust**: Content works with assistive technologies

### Legal and Business Requirements
- Ensure compliance with accessibility laws (ADA, Section 508)
- Include accessibility in design system documentation
- Provide accessibility training for development team
- Regular accessibility audits and updates

